                                            "type": "text",
                                            "content": "Figure 2. The pipeline of QR-CLIP. It has two modules: Quantity module (Sec 3.2) and Relevance module (Sec 3.3). In step 1, we add additional [CLS] to mimic different perspectives of different individuals and design the local and global loss to guide the location/time fine-tuning. Then, we freeze the fine-tuned CLIP-V and CLIP-T and use them to search for open-world knowledge from our OWK dataset (Sec 4.1). In the Relevance module, we use a scoring mechanism to weights the most valuable information from CLIP-T and CLIP-V. After multiplying the scoring weights for vision and language separately, we add them for final similarity calculation."
                                        }
