                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": "Horn's QR Theory. In cognitive research (Allott, 2013), it is believed that human reasoning is the process of obtaining the best correlations. The QR theory (Horn, 1984) builds a more clear definition of the above correlations, where Q stands for the quantity principle, which requires the maximization of valuable content, and R means the relevance principle that requires the minimization of form and extracts most related information:"
